$interpreted: Law: Miranda ye have done well. Now that thee has obtained the Holy Wooden Tablet, we shall returnth to the East.
Miranda: Thank you for your praises, Master~
Law: That ye cannot represent the Wolf Tribe, it troubles me so. But your master has no choice in the matter. What a pity...
Miranda: It's okay, Master. I understand.
Miranda: After all, you're quite a headache for the Wolf Tribe. They don't listen to you anymore, so it makes sense.
Law: Such a title, I accept with great cheer...hehe.
Law: Ah, yes. Hithering from distant lands, the Panthers are to be greatly praised. Ye must constantly show your thanks. Don't take this lightly.
Law: Has thee expressed thine thanksgivings of the heart?
Miranda: Of course. I thanked the matriach countless times. Even though she forgot my name...haha.
Miranda: It's a shame...I couldn't even bid farewell to Fatima.
Law: Miranda? Why are you standing there?
Miranda: Nothing~ Master, look at this scenery~
Law: Ye master has long since noticed this. Rarely does one come across such spectacular sights.
Law: Ah, I can feel the inspiration flowing through my bones. A perfect time for a...
Miranda: Ah!
Law: ...It appears she has awaited thine arrival.
Law: I shall walk ahead...for the scenery.
Miranda: Thank you, Master!
Fatima: You have quite the master.
Miranda: Of course. I'm doing fine as an apprentice, right?
Fatima: ...But if you're going to be the champion, there's a lot of hard work ahead.
Miranda: You're pretty strict~
Fatima: Hmph...I've come to ask you about something I'm curious about.
Miranda: Curious?
Fatima: Attending the competition, traveling to the East Alliance. It's not just to become the champion, is it?
Fatima: It has something to do with that person you mentioned?
Miranda: ......
Fatima: If you don't want to talk, I won't force you.
Miranda: No, you confided in me about not being able to dance...
Fatima: ......
Miranda: Her name is Himawari. She's a member of the Leopard Tribe.
Fatima: ...I've never heard of the Leopards before.
Miranda: Himawari says that their tribe has nearly been wiped out and that the perpetrator still roams freely in the East, committing heinous crimes.
Fatima: ......
Miranda: Besides this, she did not say much. She fell gravely ill, and told me only at the last moment.
Miranda: This power...was given to me by her.
Fatima: ......
Miranda: Before I left, she told me not to cry. She said I should smile.
Miranda: She said that she used to hate her power. All it did was cause pain and suffering, and she was unable to use it to protect anyone.
Miranda: But...she said if it were I that possessed it, perhaps something could be done...
Miranda: ...Perhaps by properly using this power, the people who need to be protected would be protected...
Fatima: ...So, you want to enter the tourney for her.
Miranda: That's right.
Miranda: I want to prove to them, for her, that the natural skill endowed upon the Leopards should continue to exist, that it has value in this world.
Fatima: I see...not something that's easy to talk about.
Miranda: Yeah...but after hearing Fatima sing yesterday, I thought I should try...to relay how I feel.
Miranda: Perhaps...the Panther God will bless me?
Fatima: I understand. Thank you for telling me this.
Fatima: Don't worry. I'll help you keep this secret. Also...I wish you a smooth journey to becoming champion.
Miranda: ...Thank you! I'll bring back the Holy Talisman as soon as I become champion!
Law: Why dost thee smirk and grin, Miranda? Your master hasn't gone deaf yet.
Miranda: Master, I hadn't noticed...
Miranda: I haven't seen you in days, and you look like your spirits have risen to the clouds. Almost like...you've become another person.
Law: Your master has had his fill of superior wine. Naturally, my spirits have been raised by the spirits. Speaking of which...hast ye turned merry as well!?
Miranda: ...Haha. Master, you're right~
Miranda: That this trip...wasn't made in vain!
